(## 2. Core Design Decisions) Tj
0 -12 Td
() Tj
0 -12 Td
(### Decision A: Separate auth planes \(Clerk for web, PAT for extension\)) Tj
0 -12 Td
(- Implemented in API deps and web forwarding:) Tj
0 -12 Td
(  - `apps/api/app/api/deps.py`) Tj
0 -12 Td
(  - `apps/web/src/lib/server-api.ts`) Tj
0 -12 Td
(- Why: low-friction extension auth for MVP while preserving standard web auth UX.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(- Tradeoff: dual auth model increases complexity and introduces trust-boundary issues.) Tj
0 -12 Td
() Tj
0 -12 Td
(### Decision B: Postgres + pgvector as single backend store) Tj
0 -12 Td
(- `apps/api/app/db/models.py`) Tj
0 -12 Td
(- `infra/db/init.sql`) Tj
0 -12 Td
(- Why: minimal infra and strong transactional semantics across metadata + vectors.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(- Tradeoff: retrieval performance tuning and horizontal scale are deferred.) Tj
0 -12 Td
() Tj
0 -12 Td
(### Decision C: Deterministic local embeddings instead of provider embeddings) Tj
0 -12 Td
(- `apps/api/app/services/embeddings.py`) Tj
0 -12 Td
(- Why: zero external dependency/cost for MVP.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(- Tradeoff: retrieval quality is materially lower than semantic embeddings.) Tj
0 -12 Td
() Tj
0 -12 Td
(### Decision D: DOM-only, user-initiated capture in extension) Tj
0 -12 Td
(- `apps/extension/content-script.js`) Tj
0 -12 Td
(- Why: explicit compliance with no background crawling / no interception.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(- Tradeoff: capture completeness depends on what is currently rendered and expanded.) Tj
0 -12 Td
() Tj
0 -12 Td
(### Decision E: Source-grounded response format with explicit Unknown / Speculation fallback) Tj
0 -12 Td
(- `apps/api/app/services/rag.py`) Tj
0 -12 Td
(- `apps/api/app/services/prompts.py`) Tj
0 -12 Td
(- Why: enforce attribution and reduce hallucination risk.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(- Tradeoff: response quality is heuristic \(no real LLM synthesis currently\).) Tj
0 -12 Td
() Tj
