(## 12. Security and Trust Boundaries) Tj
0 -12 Td
() Tj
0 -12 Td
(Critical points for senior review:) Tj
0 -12 Td
() Tj
0 -12 Td
(1. Header trust model for Clerk identity in FastAPI.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(- `/v1/tokens` trusts `x-clerk-user-id` headers and does not validate Clerk JWT.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(- Intended MVP shortcut, but directly calling API can spoof identity if endpoint is exposed.) Tj
0 -12 Td
() Tj
0 -12 Td
(2. PAT storage in extension.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(- PAT stored in `chrome.storage.sync` plaintext form.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(- Sync storage improves UX but expands token exposure surface.) Tj
0 -12 Td
() Tj
0 -12 Td
(3. CORS policy is permissive.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(- API sets `allow_origins=["*"]` and `allow_credentials=True`.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(- Should be tightened for production origins and extension context.) Tj
0 -12 Td
() Tj
0 -12 Td
(4. Token lifecycle limitations.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(- No token expiry, no scoped permissions, no rotate endpoint.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(- Revocation supported, hashing is HMAC\(pepper, token\) which is good baseline for random tokens.) Tj
0 -12 Td
() Tj
